Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the optimization of network performance, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a centralized policy, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the emulation of a queuing network, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical bounds of network performance, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
